Cocoa exports from  Ecuador , the
worldâ€™s top grower of flavored beans used in fine chocolate,
fell to 10,172 metric tons in August, a 42 percent decrease from
a year earlier.  Ecuador shipments fell from 17,627 metric tons in August
2011, according to an e-mailed statement today from the National
Cocoa Exporters Association, known as Anecacao. Exports rose
from 6,937 metric tons in July, the group said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
